        "`goseg/protocol/actions/actions.go` defines action and namespace constants (`ActionUploadOpenEndpoint`, `ActionUploadReset`, `ActionC2CConnect`, `NamespaceUpload`, `NamespaceC2C`) while `goseg/protocol/contracts/contracts.go` separately defines the canonical bindings (`ActionContractBindings`) and namespace constants, creating dual sources of truth.",
        "`buildUploadActionContracts` in `actions.go` hardcodes upload action handling with fixed keys (`ActionUploadOpenEndpoint`, `ActionUploadReset`) instead of deriving upload payload policy from the same binding source used by `contracts`, so cross-module extension requires synchronized manual edits.",
        "`ensureActionContractsInitialized` in `actions.go` performs global singleton initialization and panics on contract wiring errors, so a contract/binding defect in `contracts.go` can terminate any caller path that touches action metadata, increasing subsystem blast radius."
      ],
      "impact_scope": "subsystem",
      "fix_scope": "multi_file_refactor",
      "confidence": "high"
    }
